a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes v w proj_w_v :: "real^3"
assumes h0 : "v = vector [2, 3, -1]"
and h1 : "w = vector [2, -1, 0]"
and h2 : "proj_w_v = ((v \<bullet> w) / (w \<bullet> w)) *\<^sub>R w"
shows  "proj_w_v = vector [2/5, -1/5, 0]"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 For $\bold{v} = \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 3 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix}$ and $\bold{w} = \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -1 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}$, compute $\text{proj}_{\bold{w}} \bold{v}$. The final Answer is \begin{pmatrix} 2/5 \\ -1/5 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}
 ### Proof
 We have that \begin{align} \text{proj}_{\bold{w}} \bold{v} &= \frac{\bold{v} \cdot \bold{w}}{\bold{w} \cdot \bold{w}} \bold{w} \\ &= \frac{\begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 3 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -1 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}}{\begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -1 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -1 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}} \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -1 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix} \\
 &= \frac{1}{5} \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -1 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix} \\ &= \boxed{\begin{pmatrix} 2/5 \\ -1/5 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}}. \end{align}
 *)

theorem
fixes v w proj_w_v :: "real^3"
assumes h0 : "v = vector [2, 3, -1]"
and h1 : "w = vector [2, -1, 0]"
and h2 : "proj_w_v = ((v \<bullet> w) / (w \<bullet> w)) *\<^sub>R w"
shows  "proj_w_v = vector [2/5, -1/5, 0]"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
a_0.informal problem: Given vectors $v = [2, 3, -1]$ and $w = [2, -1, 0]$, find the projection of $v$ onto $w$. The final answer is $[2/5, -1/5, 0]$.
